eatures. Defaults to 25.\n    n_outputs (int, optional): The number of output features. Defaults to 2.\n    n_hidden_layers (int, optional): The number of hidden layers. Defaults to 2.\n    hidden_dim (int, optional): The dimensionality of the hidden layers. Defaults to 35."]}, {"name": "congrads.networks.MLPNetwork.forward", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "X", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Performs a forward pass through the network.\n\nArgs:\n    X (Tensor): The input tensor to be passed through the network.\n\nReturns:\n    dict: A dictionary containing the 'input' (original input) and\n          'output' (predicted output) of the network."]}, {"name": "congrads.networks.MLPNetwork.linear", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "in_features", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "out_features", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Creates a basic linear block with a linear transformation followed\nby a ReLU activation function.\n\nArgs:\n    in_features (int): The number of input features.\n    out_features (int): The number of output features.\n\nReturns:\n    nn.Module: A sequential module consisting of a Linear layer and ReLU activation."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A multi-layer perceptron (MLP) neural network model consisting of\nan input layer, multiple hidden layers, and an output layer.\n\nThis class constructs an MLP with configurable hyperparameters such as the\nnumber of input features, output features, number of hidden layers, and\nthe dimensionality of hidden layers. It provides methods for both\nbuilding the model and performing a forward pass through the network.\n\nAttributes:\n    n_inputs (int): The number of input features.\n    n_outputs (int): The number of output features.\n    n_hidden_layers (int): The number of hidden layers in the network.\n    hidden_dim (int): The dimensionality of the hidden layers.\n    input (nn.Module): The input layer (linear transformation followed by ReLU).\n    hidden (nn.Module): The sequential hidden layers (each consisting of\n                         a linear transformation followed by ReLU).\n    out (nn.Module): The output layer (linear transformation)."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "congrads", "documentation": ["__init__.py"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "congrads.version", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "congrads.constraints", "xref": {"fqname": "congrads..constraints", "project": null}}, {"name": "congrads.core", "xref": {"fqname": "congrads..core", "project": null}}, {"name": "congrads.datasets", "xref": {"fqname": "congrads..datasets", "project": null}}, {"name": "congrads.descriptor", "xref": {"fqname": "congrads..descriptor", "project": null}}, {"name": "congrads.metrics", "xref": {"fqname": "congrads..metrics", "project": null}}, {"name": "congrads.networks", "xref": {"fqname": "congrads..networks", "project": null}}, {"name": "congrads.utils", "xref": {"fqname": "congrads..utils", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "congrads.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "congrads.utils.splitDataLoaders", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": {"name": "Dataset", "xref": {"fqname": "torch.utils.data.Dataset", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "loader_args", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "train_loader_args", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "valid_loader_args", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "test_loader_args", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.